Quite a lot of so called 'adults' in the general public probably are still children.<br>
<br>
I wonder whether he'd accept a science court like proposal.  The idea of that would be that a panel of experts would weigh up the evidence like a jury with a moderator to make sure everyone plays by the rules and advocotes for each side presenting their cases.<br>
<br>
The moderator could then find out what each side agrees and disagrees on and then allow them to present what their view of the issue to be decided upon by the panel of experts.  The expert panel could vote either way or vote that we don't know or basically say anything they damn well like about the points then it could be released to the public to help guide their decision making.<br>
<br>
