b: They'll go in and lose anyway<br>
c: They'll go in, disrupt the whole thing and look very bad.<br>
<br>
There have been cases at which the suggestion of using a science court to resolve and issue has caused a side to back down.  When we get big and able to do it then I'd like to see it done although it may a bit of time before we can do so. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=brucetrib>brucetrib</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(3/13/02 4:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=72.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nuclear Space Article with familiar illustration</span><hr size=1> Who are we kidding, the fact remains online and offline<br>
